.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-NEW" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.26" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-new \- Write a starter compose file from a built\-in template
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose new [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Write a starter compose specification from a built\-in template, or list and describe the available templates without writing a file. Writing a template requires an explicit shared cache directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--template\fR \fITEMPLATE\fR
Built\-in template name to render.
.TP
\fB--list\-templates\fR
List the available built\-in templates and exit.
.TP
\fB--describe\-template\fR \fITEMPLATE\fR
Describe one built\-in template and exit.
.TP
\fB--name\fR \fINAME\fR
Application name written into the generated spec.
.TP
\fB--cache\-dir\fR \fICACHE_DIR\fR
Shared cache directory written into the generated spec; required when writing a template.
.TP
\fB--output\fR \fIFILE\fR
Path to the compose file to create. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--force\fR
Overwrite the output file if it already exists.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose new \-\-list\-templates
hpc\-compose new \-\-describe\-template minimal\-batch
hpc\-compose new \-\-template minimal\-batch \-\-name my\-app \-\-cache\-dir '<shared\-cache\-dir>' \-\-output compose.yaml
.fi
